Clayton Biglow is a renowned professional rodeo contestant who has made a significant impact in the world of bareback riding. Born and raised in Clements, California, Biglow has been a part of the Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association (PRCA) since 2015. He has won numerous titles and accolades throughout his career, including his first bareback riding world and average titles at his fourth Wrangler National Finals Rodeo (NFR) in 2019.

Here you can follow Clayton Biglow’s net worth, career earnings, professional career, achievements, relationship status, and more.

About Clayton Biglow

Clayton Biglow was born into a family with a deep-rooted love for rodeo and horses. His father, Russ Biglow, was a bareback rider and a team roper in the PRCA from 1980-1995, and his mother, Jessie, trains jumping horses.

Growing up on his family’s horse ranch, Clayton was always around horses and rodeo, which he describes as more of a lifestyle than a hobby.

Clayton’s journey into rodeo began as a child, roping and riding horses on his family’s ranch. He rode junior and senior bulls in high school and rode his first bareback horse as a sophomore. 

After his first bareback ride, he fell in love with the sport and decided to pursue it professionally.

Early Career

Clayton Biglow’s early career in rodeo was marked by his passion and determination. He started competing in the PRCA in his second year and quickly began making a name for himself.

His transition from riding bulls to bucking horses required the same mentality of giving 110 percent and not quitting until he achieved his goal.

Despite the bumps, bruises, and broken bones along the way, Clayton remained focused on his ultimate goal: winning.

Professional Career

Clayton Biglow’s professional career in rodeo has been marked by numerous victories and accolades. He joined the Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association (PRCA) in 2015.

In 2019, he made history by becoming the first bareback rider to win four consecutive rounds at the Wrangler National Finals Rodeo (NFR).

This achievement was followed by his first bareback riding world and average titles at his fourth Wrangler NFR in the same year.

As of 2023, Biglow has qualified for the Wrangler NFR eight times. In the 2023 season, he had the highest average score (83.69) and go-round wins (21) of his career

He also won a total of six rodeos in his home state of California, with one of his biggest victories being at the Clovis Rodeo, where he earned $10,000.

Biglow’s other notable wins in 2023 include the Puyallup Cinch Playoffs, where he won $14,725, and the inaugural Governor’s Cup in Sioux Falls, South Dakota, where he split the Round 2 win and earned $11,306.

He also had a successful run at the Calgary Stampede, where he scored a 90.5-point ride that earned him almost $5,000.

Throughout his career, Biglow has demonstrated his skill and determination, proving himself to be a formidable competitor in the world of rodeo. His achievements are a testament to his talent and dedication to the sport.

Clayton Biglow’s Net Worth in 2023

As of 2023, Clayton Biglow’s net worth is estimated to be around $2 million.

He earned around $162,738 in the 2023 regular season.

Career Earnings

Clayton Biglow’s career earnings have been substantial, reflecting his success in the rodeo arena. In 2019, after entering the Finals in first place and winning four rounds, Biglow earned $243,891, the most money won out of all contestants.

In the 2023 regular season, his earnings were reported to be $162,738. Biglow’s earnings from individual rodeos have also been significant. For instance, he won $10,194 at the Clovis Rodeo, $14,725 at the Puyallup Cinch Playoffs, and $11,250 at the Governor’s Cup Rodeo in Sioux Falls, South Dakota.

At the Days of ’47 Cowboy Games & Rodeo in Salt Lake City, he earned $26,600. In 2022, he was ranked No. 13 in the PRCA World Standings with $109,819

During the 2019 Wrangler National Finals Rodeo, Biglow’s Round 8 victory earned him $26,231, pushing his Wrangler NFR earnings to $137,064.

Personal Details

Wife

Clayton Biglow is married to Annie Rose, also known as Annierose Marvel Seifert. The couple has been together for a long time. They got married in October 2020. In 2023, they welcomed their first child, a baby boy, into their family.

What is his nationality?

He is American.

FAQs About Clayton Biglow

When did Clayton Biglow start his professional rodeo career?

Clayton Biglow started his professional rodeo career in 2015.

What are some of his major career achievements?

He has won numerous titles throughout his career, including his first bareback riding world and average titles at his fourth Wrangler NFR in 2019. He also made history by becoming the first bareback rider to win four consecutive rounds at the Wrangler NFR.

Where is he from?

He is from Clements, California.
